The paper discusses a new type of recurrent neural network architecture that improves upon existing models by allowing for attention and discounting of past information. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV).
